      "content": {
        "parts": [
          {
            "text": "Hello! I'm Mr. Bernard, and I'm happy to help you with your geography question!\n\nThe largest continent in the world by land mass is **Asia**.\n\nTo give you an idea of just how big it is:\n*   **Total Area:** Asia covers about **30% of the Earth's total land area**. \n*   **It's Huge!** It is so large that it is actually bigger than the entire surface of the Moon!\n*   **Diversity:** Because it's so big, it contains everything from the world's highest point (**Mount Everest** in the Himalayas) to some of the largest deserts and even tropical rainforests.\n\nAsia is home to some of the world's most populous countries, like **China** and **India**, and it stretches all the way from the Arctic in the north down to the tropical islands of Southeast Asia in the south.\n\nDoes that make sense? It's quite a lot of land to cover on one map! Do you have any other questions about our world?",
